body: Hmm, the hitch is that some entries live in `test` but are actually part of `build: tool` (in particular, `grpc_create_jwt`, `grpc_verify_jwt`, and `grpc_print_google_default_creds_token`. There's no problem building these under make or bazel, but cmake seems to have a problem linking them with `grpc_test_util`. Anyone seen this?
I think I realized the work-around for my previous question. Hoping that the last commit does the job.
Will not merge until grpc/proposal#56 lands, which is Feb 8 at the earliest
